I have a 50 round box of Winchester Ranger SXT, Controlled Expansion, 45 Automatic +P, 230 GR, product code Winchester RA45SXTP, designated Law Enforcement Ammunition. 

My research indicates this ammo to be first generation Ranger SXT ammo in a +P load. After Winchester pulled the Black Talon SXT name off the market due to bad media, they renamed the ammo Ranger SXT and re marketed it. 

This ammo is packaged in a 50 round (white and red box), bearing the description “Ranger SXT Controlled Expansion”.  The ammo has the black lubalox coated bullet with six talons seated in a brass case and from my research, is nearly the same bullet design as the original black talon.  The other difference is the original Talon had a nickel plated case and the Ranger SXT has brass.  It is packaged in the white and red box bearing the description  "Ranger SXT CONTROLLED EXPANSION".

I acquired this ammo in the mid-late 90’s and it has been stored inside most all the time.
